feat: Enhance file management features and improve upload session handling
- Updated file handler to include new endpoints for creating empty files and retrieving file information. - Implemented file management logic in the service layer, including methods for creating empty files and updating file content. - Refactored upload session handling to ensure proper session management and error handling. - Improved logging for better debugging and tracing of file operations. - Adjusted router to register new file-related routes and modified existing upload routes for clarity. - Enhanced error handling and validation throughout the file service and repository layers.
feat: 实现文件上传功能，包括创建上传会话、上传文件块和删除上传会话的API
feat: 更新文件服务，支持排序、过滤和分页功能，优化响应结构

Refactor response handling and implement file management features
- Migrate response handling from handler package to pkg/response for better organization and reusability. - Update all handlers to utilize the new response package for success and failure responses. - Introduce FileHandler to manage file-related HTTP requests, including fetching file lists based on URI. - Implement FileService and FileRepository to handle business logic and database interactions for file management. - Create domain model for FileItem to represent file data in a structured way. - Develop URI parsing logic to support custom URI schemes for file access. - Enhance middleware to securely manage user claims and permissions for file access. - Add necessary database models and repository methods to support file operations.
